<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 4:30PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Bay
County through 500 PM EDT...
At 429 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rhodes, or 9 miles west of Pinconning, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Pinconning and Linwood around 450 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Crump, Mount Forest
and Willard.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
